# Add a gene symbol column and rowsum to the matrix:
count_matrix <- cbind(gene = ids$SYMBOL, count_matrix, sum = rowSums(count_matrix))
# Order the countmatrix on the sum of counts:
tmp <- count_matrix[order(count_matrix$gene, count_matrix$sum, decreasing = FALSE),]

# Filter both matrices on the unique genes, selecting the ID with highest sum over all samples:
count_matrix <- tmp[!duplicated(tmp$gene, fromLast = TRUE), ]
tpm_matrix <- tpm_matrix[rownames(count_matrix),]

# Transfer the gene symbols:
rownames(count_matrix) <- count_matrix$gene
count_matrix <- count_matrix[,!colnames(count_matrix) %in% c("gene","sum")]
rownames(tpm_matrix) <- rownames(count_matrix)

rm(tmp)
## Select only genes with expression of above 10 in all samples together
count_matrix <- count_matrix[rowSums(count_matrix) >= 100,]
tpm_matrix <- tpm_matrix[rownames(count_matrix),]

Calculate CPM

## CPM matrix, not corrected for gene-length:
cpm_matrix <- apply(count_matrix, 2, function(x) (x/sum(x))*1000000) 
cpm_log_matrix <- log(cpm_matrix + 1)
write.table(cpm_matrix, paste0(resultsdir,"/GRCh38-CPM.tsv"), row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, sep= "\t", quote = FALSE)
write.table(cpm_log_matrix, paste0(resultsdir,"/GRCh38-CPM_log.tsv"), row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, sep= "\t", quote = FALSE)
write.table(count_matrix, paste0(resultsdir,"/GRCh38-counts.tsv"), row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, sep= "\t", quote = FALSE)
write.table(tpm_matrix, paste0(resultsdir,"/GRCh38-TPM_salmon.tsv"), row.names = TRUE, col.names = NA, sep= "\t", quote = FALSE)

Make DESeq objects and retrieve all comparisons of interest:

original_dds <- dds
# Making the comparisons between all Twente en Leiden samples: 
padj_tresh <- p_adj
log2FC_tresh <- 0 # 0.05

count_list <- list()
meta_list <- list()
dds_list <- list()
dds_list_lrt <- list()
rld_list <- list()
plot_list <- list()
plot_list1 <- list()
cor_list <- list()
results_list <- list()

for (target in tfs){
  for (lineage in c("VM","AM")){
    if (lineage=="VM"){
      print(lineage)
      dds <- dds_vm
      } else {
        print(lineage)
        dds <- dds_am
      }
   for (ct in c("TRAC")){#,"CT"
      ## Select per condition, filter the datasets on these samples:
      cond <- paste(target,ct,lineage, sep="_")
      print(cond)
      subset <- colnames(dds)[grepl(ct, colnames(dds)) | grepl(target, colnames(dds))]
      subset <- subset[grepl(lineage, subset)]
      print(subset)

      dds_list[[cond]] <- dds[,subset]
      rld_list[[cond]] <- rld[,subset]#(dds_list[[target]], blind = F)
      
      dds_list[[cond]]$condition <- droplevels(dds_list[[cond]]$condition)
      ## Store DE-genes between selected conditions:
      comparison<-unique(dds_list[[cond]]$condition)
      print(comparison)
      
      ## Add contrasts in the right order:
      result_table <- results(dds_list[[cond]],c("condition",as.character(c(comparison[grep(target, comparison)],comparison[grepl(ct, comparison)]))))
      result_table <- result_table[which(abs(result_table$log2FoldChange) > log2FC_tresh & result_table$padj < padj_tresh),]
      results_list[[cond]] <- result_table[order(result_table$padj, decreasing = F),]
      print(nrow(results_list[[cond]]))
      write.csv(results_list[[cond]], paste0(resultsdir, "/", cond,"_Wald_significant.csv"), quote = F)

      ## Visualize sample differences, per condition:

      plot_list[[cond]]<-DESeq2::plotPCA(rld_list[[cond]], intgroup = c("condition")) + theme_classic()
      nudge <- position_nudge(y = 1)
      plot_list1[[cond]]<-DESeq2::plotPCA(rld_list[[cond]], intgroup = c("condition")) + theme_classic() + geom_label(aes(label = name), position = nudge)

      pdf(paste0(resultsdir, "/PCAplot_bothLineages_", target, ".pdf"))
      print(plot_list[[cond]])
      dev.off()

   
    }
    
  }
}
